706726f-c.title: Brooklyn: Sheepshead Bay Road - 6th Street (West)
706726f-c.text:
Sheepshead Bay Road, north side, between West 6th and 8th Streets,
showing a rear view. Also seen is the rear of the Oceanic HEotel
which was the original Coney Island House. It was built in 1829 and
stood on Neptune Ave., opposite Shell Road, south of Coney Island Creek.
This property was sold by a road Company to John and Albert TTerhunef
later owned by Peter Lott. One Tooker was the first keeper of the house
0thers who either owned or operated the house were James W. Cropsey in
1834; Cropsey and Woglom from 1835-1843; A. Fetter, S.W. Fetter, and
John I. Snediker in the 1870s and 1880s. In the Brooklyn Atlas, it is
now looated at No. 2866 Wost 6th Street, west side, between Neptune Ave.,
and Sheepshead Bay Road.
December 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
The same, viewed from Sheepshead Bay Road.
Ootober 1928.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
